&lt;b&gt;Improv Poetry&lt;/b&gt;
During this event all participants will be given a set of requirements they must fulfill when improving a poem. Each participant will be given some time (( 5-10 minuets )) to draft his or her poem before reciting it. The poem must have a minimum of at least six lines, with at least four words to each line. Any topic or style (so long as it satisfied the other requirements) will be accepted.

&lt;b&gt;Partner Poem Improv&lt;/b&gt;
Partners will randomly be selected from the group of participants. You and your partner must improvise a poem, trading off each line, or every two lines. The poem must have some sort of rhyming scheme and be at 8-12 lines in length. A different theme will be selected for each duo.


